itles":[]},"2":{"title":"Core Features","content":"🚀 Physics Simulation Engine — Frame-rate normalized via Delta Time, eliminating speed differences across 60Hz/90Hz/120Hz screens for consistent inertia feel📱 Axis Locking — Automatically determines gesture intent, filters diagonal jitter, locks each gesture to a single axis🔄 Smart Edge Detection — Automatically yields control back to the browser when scrolling reaches boundaries, compatible with iOS swipe-back and other native behaviors🛑 Emergency Stop Click Protection — Distinguishes between \"user wants to click\" and \"user wants to brake\", only blocks click events during high-speed inertia scrolling to prevent accidental taps🖐️ Multi-finger Tracking — Locks the active finger via Touch ID, preventing coordinate jumps caused by multi-finger alternation⚡ Dirty Value Detection — Only triggers rendering and event dispatching when scroll position actually changes, avoiding unnecessary overhead🔧 UI Library Presets — Built-in preset configurations for Element Plus, Ant Design Vue, Naive UI, VxeTable, and more🎯 Zero Dependencies — Pure native implementation, no extra dependencies needed","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"3":{"title":"Use Cases","content":"Element Plus el-table componentAnt Design Vue a-table componentNaive UI n-data-table componentVxeTable, Arco Design, PrimeVue, Vuetify table componentsAny custom table that needs optimized mobile touch scrolling","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"4":{"title":"Installation","content":"","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"5":{"title":"Quick Start","content":"","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"6":{"title":"Global Registration","content":"","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","Quick Start"]},"7":{"title":"Usage in Templates","content":"","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","Quick Start"]},"8":{"title":"What Problems Does It Solve","content":"When using desktop Table components directly on mobile, you typically encounter these issues: Unresponsive Scrolling — Native overflow: auto performs poorly in some UI libraries' nested table structures, causing sluggish or completely broken touch draggingNo Inertia Feedback — No inertia scrolling after releasing, users must drag repeatedly to reach the target positionHeader Scroll Tearing — Table header fails to sync when the body scrolls, causing visual misalignmentInconsistent Feel Across Devices — Inertia distances differ between 60Hz and 120Hz screens, unable to provide a unified interaction experienceGesture Conflicts — Cannot trigger iOS swipe-back and other native browser behaviors after scrolling to boundaries v-table-touch-scroll solves these problems by intercepting the touch event flow and implementing a complete scroll physics engine inside the directive. Here are the key approaches:","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"9":{"title":"Touch History Queue","content":"Uses sliding window sampling instead of traditional weighted averages, keeping only touch points from the last 50ms to calculate release velocity, fundamentally eliminating sampling jitter on low-end devices and over-dense sampling on high refresh rate screens:","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","What Problems Does It Solve"]},"10":{"title":"Frame Rate Normalization","content":"Physics decay during inertia is normalized via Delta Time, ensuring the same swipe produces identical scroll distances on both 60Hz and 120Hz screens:","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","What Problems Does It Solve"]},"11":{"title":"Synchronous Event Dispatching","content":"Combined with dirty value detection, proactively dispatches scroll events to force immediate header synchronization, solving the visual tearing caused by asynchronous native scroll events:","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","What Problems Does It Solve"]},"12":{"title":"Edge Detection","content":"Automatically yields control when scrolling reaches container boundaries, ensuring native behaviors like iOS swipe-back are not blocked:","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","What Problems Does It Solve"]},"13":{"title":"Next Steps","content":"Check the Usage Guide for detailed configuration optionsBrowse Examples to see real-world use cases","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"14":{"title":"Configuration","content":"Learn how to use Vue Table Touch Scroll","titles":[]},"15":{"title":"Usage Guide","content":"This page covers common usage patterns for the v-table-touch-scroll directive. For complete configuration options and type definitions, see the API Reference.","titles":[]},"16":{"title":"Global Registration","content":"","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"17":{"title":"Local Registration","content":"If you don't need global registration, you can import the directive directly in a component:","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"18":{"title":"Using UI Library Presets","content":"For UI libraries with built-in presets, simply pass the preset name — no need to manually find scroll container selectors: For the full list of supported presets and their selectors, see API Reference - TablePreset.","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"19":{"title":"Using Custom Selectors","content":"For UI libraries without built-in presets, use selector to specify the scroll container inside the table: selector takes priority over preset. If both are provided, the element specified by selector will be used. If neither is provided, the directive's bound element itself is used as the scroll container.","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"20":{"title":"Custom Physics Parameters","content":"Adjust friction and drag threshold based on your use case:","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"21":{"title":"Dynamic Control","content":"Pass false to completely disable the directive, useful for toggling based on device type: You can also use the enabled property:","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"22":{"title":"Lifecycle Callbacks","content":"","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"23":{"title":"Parameters","content":"API reference for Vue Table Touch Scroll","titles":[]},"24":{"title":"API Reference","content":"","titles":[]},"25":{"title":"Directive","content":"","titles":["API Reference"]},"26":{"title":"vTableTouchScroll","content":"A Vue 3 custom directive that adds touch scroll support to table elements. Global Registration: Local Import:","titles":["API Reference","Directive"]},"27":{"title":"Type Definitions","content":"","titles":["API Reference"]},"28":{"title":"TableTouchScrollOptions","content":"Configuration options interface for the directive. PropertyTypeDefaultDescriptionenabledbooleantrueWhether to enable touch scrollingpresetTablePreset-UI library preset name, automatically applies the corresponding scroll container selectorselectorstring-CSS selector for the target scroll element, takes priority over presetfrictionnumber0.95Friction/decay rate. Higher = slower decay (smoother scrolling), lower = faster stop (range: 0.8 - 0.99)dragThresholdnumber5Displacement threshold (px) before determining scroll direction, distinguishes minor jitter from intentional draggingdisableInertiabooleanfalseWhether to disable inertia scrolling. When true, scrolling stops immediately on finger releaseclickBlockThresholdnumber0.5Speed threshold (px/ms) for emergency stop click blocking. Higher = more lenient, lower = more strict (range: 0.3 - 1.0)onScrollStart() => void-Callback fired when scrolling starts, after finger displacement exceeds dragThreshold and direction is lockedonScrollEnd() => void-Callback fired when scrolling ends, after inertia animation fully stops Scroll container priority: selector > preset > the directive's bound element. Full Type Signature:","titles":["API Reference","Type Definitions"]},"29":{"title":"TablePreset","content":"Supported UI library preset types and their corresponding scroll container selectors. PresetUI LibrarySelector'element-plus'Element Plus.el-scrollbar__wrap'ant-design-vue'Ant Design Vue.ant-table-body'arco-design'Arco Design.arco-table-body'naive-ui'Naive UI.n-scrollbar-container'primevue'PrimeVue.p-datatable-table-container'vuetify'Vuetify.v-table__wrapper tbody'vxe-table'VxeTable.vxe-table--body-inner-wrapper","titles":["API Reference","Type Definitions"]},"30":{"title":"Exports","content":"","titles":["API Reference"]},"31":{"title":"UI_LIBRARY_SELECTORS","content":"UI library selector preset mapping constant.","titles":["API Reference","Exports"]},"32":{"title":"getSelectorByPreset","content":"Get the corresponding CSS selector by preset name. Parameters ParameterTypeDescriptionpresetTablePresetUI library preset name Returns string | undefined — The corresponding CSS selector, or undefined if the preset does not exist.","titles":["API Reference","Exports"]},"33":{"title":"Internal Physics Engine Parameters","content":"Physics engine constants used internally by the directive (not externally configurable): ConstantValueDescriptionDEFAULT_FRICTION0.95Default friction/decay rateMIN_VELOCITY0.05Velocity threshold (px/ms) to stop inertia animationMAX_DT32Max frame interval limit (ms), prevents jumps after frame dropsDEFAULT_DRAG_THRESHOLD5Default drag detection threshold (px)INERTIA_STOP_DELAY80Inertia protection delay (ms). If finger pauses longer than this before release, inertia is not triggeredSAFE_CLICK_VELOCITY0.5Default speed threshold (px/ms) for emergency stop click blocking","titles":["API Reference"]},"34":{"title":"Element Plus","content":"Using Vue Table Touch Scroll with Element Plus tables","titles":[]},"35":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"","titles":["Element Plus"]},"36":{"title":"Basic Usage","content":"","titles":["Element Plus"]},"37":{"title":"Ant Design Vue","content":"Using Vue Table Touch Scroll with Ant Design Vue tables","titles":[]},"38":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"","titles":["Ant Design Vue"]},"39":{"title":"Basic Usage","content":"","titles":["Ant Design Vue"]},"40":{"title":"Naive UI","content":"Using Vue Table Touch Scroll with Naive UI tables","titles":[]},"41":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"","titles":["Naive UI"]},"42":{"title":"Basic Usage","content":"","titles":["Naive UI"]},"43":{"title":"VxeTable","content":"Using Vue Table Touch Scroll with VxeTable","titles":[]},"44":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"","titles":["VxeTable"]},"45":{"title":"Basic Usage","content":"","titles":["VxeTable"]},"46":{"title":"Other Libraries","content":"Using Vue Table Touch Scroll with other UI libraries or custom tables","titles":[]},"47":{"title":"Other UI Libraries","content":"Vue Table Touch Scroll supports Table components from all desktop Vue UI component libraries. For libraries with built-in presets, see the API Reference and use preset for quick integration:","titles":["Other Libraries"]},"48":{"title":"No Preset? Use Selector","content":"For libraries without built-in presets, use selector to specify the actual scrollable container element inside the table. You'll need to use browser DevTools to find the CSS selector for the DOM element responsible for scrolling: If you'd like to add built-in preset support for a UI library, feel free to submit an Issue or PR on GitHub.","titles":["Other Libraries"]},"49":{"title":"Home","content":"Vue Table Touch Scrollvue-table-touch-scroll is a lightweight solution dedicated to bridging the gap between desktop tables and mobile touch interactions. With a simple directive, it ensures that any Vue PC table component delivers a native-grade, silky-smooth scrolling and interaction experience on mobile devices. This includes seamless out-of-the-box support for table components in mainstream UI libraries like Element Plus, Ant Design Vue, and Naive UI.","titles":[]},"50":{"title":"介绍","content":"vue-table-touch-scroll 是一个轻量级解决方案，专门用于弥合 桌面表格组件 与 移动端触摸交互 之间的体验差距。通过一个简单的指令，它可以让任何 Vue PC 表格组件在移动设备上也能获得 接近原生级、丝滑流畅的滚动与交互体验。该方案开箱即用地支持主流 UI 库中的表格组件，例如：Element Plus、Ant Design Vue、Naive UI，让这些桌面端表格在移动端也能实现顺畅的触摸滚动体验。","titles":[]},"51":{"title":"Vue Table Touch Scroll","content":"vue-table-touch-scroll 是一个轻量级解决方案，专门用于弥合 桌面表格组件 与 移动端触摸交互 之间的体验差距。通过一个简单的指令，它可以让任何 Vue PC 表格组件在移动设备上也能获得 接近原生级、丝滑流畅的滚动与交互体验。该方案开箱即用地支持主流 UI 库中的表格组件，例如：Element Plus、Ant Design Vue、Naive UI，让这些桌面端表格在移动端也能实现顺畅的触摸滚动体验。","titles":[]},"52":{"title":"核心特性","content":"🚀 物理仿真引擎 — 基于 Delta Time 的帧率归一化，消除 60Hz/90Hz/120Hz 屏幕的速度差异，提供一致的惯性体感📱 方向轴锁定 — 自动判定手势意图，过滤对角线抖动，每次手势只锁定在一个轴向🔄 智能边缘感知 — 滚动触达边界时自动交还控制权给浏览器，兼容 iOS 侧滑返回等原生行为🛑 急停点击保护 — 区分\"用户想点击\"与\"用户想刹车\"，仅在高速惯性滚动时拦截点击事件，防止误触🖐️ 多指追踪 — 通过 Touch ID 追踪锁定活跃手指，防止多指交替导致的坐标跳变⚡ 脏值检测 — 仅在滚动位置实际变化时触发渲染和事件派发，避免无效开销🔧 UI 库预设 — 内置 Element Plus、Ant Design Vue、Naive UI、VxeTable 等主流 UI 库的预设配置🎯 零依赖 — 纯原生实现，无需额外依赖","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"53":{"title":"适用场景","content":"Element Plus 的 el-table 组件Ant Design Vue 的 a-table 组件Naive UI 的 n-data-table 组件VxeTable、Arco Design、PrimeVue、Vuetify 等表格组件任何需要优化移动端触摸滚动的自定义表格","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"54":{"title":"安装","content":"","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"55":{"title":"快速开始","content":"","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"56":{"title":"全局注册","content":"","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","快速开始"]},"57":{"title":"在模板中使用","content":"","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","快速开始"]},"58":{"title":"解决了什么问题","content":"在移动端直接使用桌面端 Table 组件时，通常会遇到以下问题： 滚动不跟手 — 原生 overflow: auto 在部分 UI 库的表格嵌套结构中表现不佳，触摸拖拽时响应迟钝或完全无法滚动缺少惯性反馈 — 松手后没有惯性滑动，用户需要反复拖拽才能到达目标位置表头滚动撕裂 — 表体滚动时表头未能同步更新，产生视觉错位不同设备体感差异 — 60Hz 和 120Hz 屏幕上的惯性距离不一致，无法提供统一的交互体验手势冲突 — 滚动到边界后无法触发 iOS 侧滑返回等浏览器原生行为 v-table-touch-scroll 通过接管触摸事件流，在指令内部实现了一套完整的滚动物理引擎来解决上述问题。以下是几个核心方案：","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll"]},"59":{"title":"历史轨迹队列","content":"采用滑动窗口采样替代传统的加权平均，仅保留最近 50ms 内的触摸点来计算松手速度，从根源上消除低端机采样抖动和高刷屏幕采样过密的影响：","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","解决了什么问题"]},"60":{"title":"帧率归一化","content":"惯性阶段的物理衰减基于 Delta Time 归一化，使得同一次滑动在 60Hz 和 120Hz 屏幕上产生相同的滚动距离：","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","解决了什么问题"]},"61":{"title":"同步事件派发","content":"配合脏值检测，主动派发 scroll 事件强制表头即时同步，解决原生 scroll 异步导致的视觉撕裂：","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","解决了什么问题"]},"62":{"title":"边缘感知","content":"当滚动触达容器边界时自动交还控制权，确保 iOS 侧滑返回等原生行为不被阻断：","titles":["Vue Table Touch Scroll","解决了什么问题"]},"63":{"title":"下